<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="700" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="129.[2089,2675,2195,2620]" pageId="129" pageNumber="700">
Previously classified as a subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1871" box="[2089,2176,2313,2346]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Naemorhedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="129" pageNumber="700" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">griseus</taxonomicName>
. The generic name was originally spelled 
<taxonomicName box="[2216,2387,2352,2385]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Naemorhedus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="129" pageNumber="700" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Naemorhedus</taxonomicName>
, but the spelling 
<taxonomicName box="[2090,2261,2392,2425]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Nemorhaedus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="129" pageNumber="700" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Nemorhaedus</taxonomicName>
, despite being an unjustified emendation, is “in prevailing” usage and is used here. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="700" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6512789" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6512789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6512789/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="700" targetBox="[1472,2065,2203,2619]" targetPageId="129">
